The paper presents a novel algorithm for motion and trajectory planning for nonholonomic mobile robots using deep reinforcement learning. This involves processing a continuous state space and executing continuous actions, which are key areas of research in robotics and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.RO (Robotics and Control). Additionally, the use of deep reinforcement learning suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The consideration of kinematic and dynamic constraints suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the evaluation of the algorithm in a simulation environment suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
